Ivi Very important CSS concepts
1. Box model(Every HTML element is a box)
It has: content, padding,  border, margin

Example:
.card {
  padding: 20px;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  margin: 20px;
}

padding -> space inside the box
border -> line around the box
margin -> space outside the box

2. Class vs ID
## Class (Use class for reusable styling)
#HTML
<div class="card">Card 1</div>
<div class="card">Card 2</div>
# CSS
.card {
  background-color: white;
  padding: 20px;
}

## ID [Use ID for one unique element]
#HTML
<div id="main-header">Header</div>
# CSS
#main-header {
  background-color: black;
} -> Advice entantee use classes most of the time, avoid too many IDs in CSS folks

3. Flexbox [Flexbox is used for alignment]
# Example:
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}

